   "source": [
    "# 🧭 Cross-Absolute Selection Principle (CASP)\n",
    "## Comprehensive Theoretical Framework of Absolute Interaction Mechanics\n",
    "\n",
    "### 📘 Formal Definition\n",
    "> **Definition (CASP):** A mediated interaction between two Absolute Entities is valid if and only if it:\n",
    "> 1. Minimizes cross-absolute interaction action\n",
    "> 2. Maintains entropic compatibility within tolerance δ\n",
    "> 3. Maximizes directional coherence\n",
    "> Subject to irreducibility and transfinite interaction constraints.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔬 Ontological Context\n",
    "This notebook extends the theoretical groundwork established in `05_transfinite_interaction_chains.ipynb`, providing a rigorous computational framework for evaluating cross-absolute interactions.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🌐 Theoretical Lineage\n",
    "Derived from the **Enhanced Mathematical Ontology of Absolute Nothingness**, CASP represents a fundamental constraint system governing potential interactions between irreducible ontological entities.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📊 Foundational Postulates\n",
    "\n",
    "### Postulate I: Minimal Interaction Action\n",
    "**Ontological Derivation:** Emerges from the principle of minimal ontological perturbation in irreducible systems.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\mathcal{A}_{\\text{min}} = \\arg \\min_{M \\in \\mathcal{M}} \\| S_1 M S_2^T \\|_F $$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Interpretation:** The Frobenius norm represents the total projected ontological action in finite embedding, quantifying cross-absolute interaction intensity.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Postulate II: Entropic Compatibility\n",
    "**Ontological Derivation:** Ensures entropy conservation across mediation processes.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\delta_{\\text{entropy}} = \\frac{|\\epsilon_1 - \\mathrm{Tr}(I I^T)|}{\\epsilon_1} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Constraint:** Interaction is only permissible if $\\delta_{\\text{entropy}} \\leq 10^{-6}$\n",
    "\n",
    "### Postulate III: Directional Coherence Maximization\n",
    "**Ontological Derivation:** Captures informational alignment and potential for meaningful interaction.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\text{CI} = \\cos(\\langle S_1 M, S_2 \\rangle) $$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Coherence Index (CI):** Bounded in $[-1, 1]$, representing directional information transfer potential"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "core-imports",
   "metadata": {},
